Front sight is integrated with gas block; Rear sight includes “RPK” style windage adjustment; Features factory installed UTG Picatinny handguard rail; M+M Chaos billet flash hider / muzzle brake; Factory side rail mount; Tapco G-2 trigger and retaining plate; Hogue pistol grip. One of the first things I noticed about the M10 when I picked it up was that it’s fairly light for an AK. The rifle weighs in at only 7.3 pounds. The overall length of the gun is 36″ with the fixed “Warsaw Pact” length stock. Unlike a lot of the AKs on the market these days, the M+M M10 isn’t a parts kit gun. Rather, it’s made from all new parts. The M10 includes a UTG quad rail. Although I generally believe UTG products provide a lot of value for the buck. The M10-762 features a new, Romanian-made, cold-hammer forged, chrome-lined 16.25″ barrel. The rear sight is probably one of the best features on the M+M. On most AK variants, the rear sight is adjustable for elevation only, using a sliding “ramp.” (above right). The M+M has that same feature – in this case graduated to 1000 meters in 100 meter increments – but it also adds an RPK-type rear sight, which is adjustable for windage another feature on the M10-762 is the front sight, which is integrated with the gas block . According to M+M, the M10-762 is manufactured out of brand new high quality parts  everything is newly manufactured to be US 922(r) compliant. The receiver and major parts are made in Romania by F.A. Cugir, the main military arsenal in Romania. However I modified my M10 and put on the slide fire stock making it a legal functioning fully automatic rifle once you learn how to use it. There are a lot of youtube videos showing how to use it, it was a $300 add on. I have also added a detachable with quick release 2.5-10x40 duel Illuminated scope with a gree laser, another $150 add on, plus full size heavy duty 7'' to 11'' bipod, another $50 add on, also comes with 4-30rd tapco mags another $40 add on and a $20 AK cleaning kit. My total amount invested is $1260.00 Plus I have 900 rds of Brown Bear hp ammo that I will through in for $150 if you want it. As the photo shows I still have the original stock plus another aftermarket stock im throwin in with the deal, and can't forget about the speed loader im throwing in with it also. If you want everything pictured i'll take $1350, if you just want what is pictured without the ammo i'll take $1200. Contact Dave at nine three seven four zero two four six three six.

This is a new, hard to find Keltec PMR30 22 Magnum Pistol with 30 Round Magazine.  This gun has a Lifetime Replacement Warranty.  This is not a repair warranty, this is a replacement with a new, not refurbished gun.

The PMR-30 is a light weight, full size pistol chambered for the flat-shooting .22Magnum cartridge (.22WMR). The PMR-30 operates on a unique hybrid blowback/locked-breech system. This operation system allows for the use of a wide variety of ammunition as it seamlessly adjusts between locked breach and blowback operation, depending on the pressure of the cartridge. It uses a double stack magazine of a new design that holds 30 rounds and fits completely in the grip of the pistol. The trigger is a crisp single action with an over-travel stop. The manual safety is a thumb activated ambidextrous safety lever (up for SAFE, down for FIRE). The slide locks back after the last shot and a manual slide lock lever is also provided. The light, crisp trigger pull and fiber optic sights make the PMR-30 ideal for target shooting and hunting small game.

Slide and barrel are 4140 steel, frame is 7075 aluminum. Grip, slide cover, trigger, mag release, and safety levers are glass reinforced Nylon (Zytel), much like other Kel-Tec Pistols. Magazine is Also Zytel and holds 30 rounds, with round count ports. Other features include: dual opposing extractors for reliability, heel magazine release to aid in magazine retention, dovetailed aluminum front sight, Picatinny accessory rail under the barrel, Urethane recoil buffer, captive coaxial recoil springs. PMR30 disassembles for cleaning by removal of a single pin.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Mossberg US 44 .22 LR Military Target Rifle U.S. Property
postcontent:
Rifle is in great condition, has been drilled and tapped for the scope.  Scope is a BSA .22 Special.  Includes one magazine. It has a gray parkerized finish.

Military markings as follows:
    US PROPERTY marked on barrel, receiver
    Serial Number on barrel, receiver
    Ordnance ball cartouche stamped in stock 

The U.S. 44 .22 caliber rifle manufactured by Mossberg for the U.S. Military. It is similar to the M42 and M44 commercial rifles and many parts are interchangeable. With the proper magazine, you can use .22 short, .22 long, and .22 LR in this rifle. Without the magazine, you can use it as a single-shot rifle, the magazine holds seven (7) rounds. The rifle has a bull barrel with recessed muzzle; the trigger is not adjustable, the front sight is fixed. The barrel is "lead-lapped" which is a process that fills in the micro-cracks in the metal producing a very smooth surface with very little variance or imperfections. It is also very labor intensive and, as a result, expensive. The process is only applied to the most expensive target rifles these days. The rifles were manufactured 1943-1946. 



Trigger guard has some minor damage, missing the red & green fire & safe indicators.
